            {
                "comment": "Professor is very knowledgeable, but I cannot recommend this class. Does NOT reflect 2 credit course at all, it should be 3 credits. Grade depends on 4 very challenging exam, not taken in class, 2 hours long, after school hours. Tested on very specific details, many short essays, T/F, and labeling structures. I advise immunology course prior.",
                "difficulty_rating": 5,
                "quality_rating": 3
            },
            {
                "comment": "Graded based solely on the 4 exams, and the exams are not multiple choice. They consist of drawing random structures, many free response questions on incredibly detailed topics, and a couple T/F or matching problems. Exams expect you to remember even the tiniest details talked about in class, and the class jam packed of material, terms and details.",
                "difficulty_rating": 4,
                "quality_rating": 2
